    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-quality 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. This specimen maintains exceptional compression across all rotor faces, with a vacuum system free of the common 'black box' degradation. The drivetrain remains factory-spec, utilizing the original 5-speed short-throw transmission and Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis integrity is absolute, preserving the 50/50 weight distribution and aluminum double-wishbone suspension geometry. Every bushing, seal, and cooling component is in peak operational state, ensuring no heat-soak issues or thermal fatigue. A true turnkey investment for the JDM purist.",
